names of famous designers, because the designs themselves can be
bootlegged easily and with impunity. The only way to make clothing that
cannot be legally bootlegged is to print copyrighted and trademarked
words on it; once you have taken that step the clothing itself doesn't
really matter, and so a t-shirt is as good as anything else. T-shirts
with expensive words on them are now the insignia of the upper class.
T-shirts with cheap words, or no words at all, are for the commoners.
    --Neil Stephenson, "In the Beginning was the Command Line"
