Functor allows only applying pure functions on effectual.
Applicative allows lifting into effectual and combining* effectual values.
Monad adds selection of effectuals according to their internal values.
    -- sinelaw, on #haskell, after Peaker
* Note: 'combining' means 'sequencing' here, of course....
